# Coding Style

## Purpose

Keep code consistent, readable, and aligned with existing patterns.

## When It Applies

All `.ts` and `.tsx` files. See also `docs/CODING_GUIDE.md`.

## Requirements

- TypeScript strict mode; no `any` unless documented with a reason.
- Prefer `interface` for object shapes; `type` for unions and utilities.
- Use `@repo/ui` components; use `cn()` for conditional classes.
- Server Components by default; add `'use client'` only when needed.
- Throw `BaseError` subclasses in services; convert to `ApiResponse` in routes.
- Match existing import order: external → workspace → relative.

## Examples

```typescript
// ✅ Typed, minimal scope
export function formatUserName(user: User): string {
  return user.fullName ?? user.email;
}

// ✅ Client boundary explicit
'use client';
export function ThemeToggle() { /* ... */ }
```

## Bad Examples

```typescript
// ❌ any escape hatch
function handle(data: any) {}

// ❌ Inline styles when Tailwind token exists
<div style={{ color: '#333' }} />

// ❌ Catching and swallowing errors
try { await save(); } catch (e) { return null; }
```
